# ðŸ“˜ MySQL DDL Commands Documentation

This repository is a quick guide for MySQL beginners to learn and practice **DDL (Data Definition Language)** commands.  
DDL defines the **structure** of databases, tables, and objects.

---

## ðŸ“Œ 1. Create Database & Table
```sql
-- Create database
CREATE DATABASE ash;

-- Show databases
SHOW DATABASES;

-- Select database
USE ash;

-- Create table with constraints
CREATE TABLE ak (
    sid INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    sname VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    age INT CHECK (age > 18)
);
ðŸ“Œ 2. Insert & View Data
INSERT INTO ak (sname, age) VALUES ('Akash', 21);
INSERT INTO ak (sname, age) VALUES ('Vasu', 21);

SELECT * FROM ak;

ðŸ“Œ 3. ALTER TABLE (Modify Structure)

Add column

ALTER TABLE ak ADD COLUMN ph_no INT NOT NULL;


Add column after specific column

ALTER TABLE ak ADD COLUMN id INT AFTER age;


Rename column

ALTER TABLE ak RENAME COLUMN ph_no TO phone;


Modify datatype

ALTER TABLE ak MODIFY phone CHAR(20);


Drop columns

ALTER TABLE ak DROP COLUMN phone, DROP COLUMN email;

ðŸ“Œ 4. DROP, TRUNCATE, DELETE

Drop table

DROP TABLE ak;


Truncate table (clear data only)

TRUNCATE TABLE ak;


Delete rows selectively

DELETE FROM ak WHERE age < 20;

ðŸ“Œ 5. Rename Table
RENAME TABLE ak TO KrsnaDas;

ðŸ“Œ 6. Practice Task: Employees Table
CREATE DATABASE officedb;
USE officedb;

CREATE TABLE employees (
    eid INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    ename VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL
);

ALTER TABLE employees ADD COLUMN gender CHAR(1) AFTER ename;
ALTER TABLE employees ADD COLUMN salary INT;
ALTER TABLE employees ADD COLUMN role VARCHAR(20) AFTER gender;

ALTER TABLE employees RENAME COLUMN role TO erole;
ALTER TABLE employees DROP COLUMN erole;

RENAME TABLE employees TO emp;
DROP TABLE emp;

âœ… Summary

CREATE â†’ make DB objects

ALTER â†’ change structure

DROP â†’ remove permanently

TRUNCATE â†’ delete all rows (keep structure)

RENAME â†’ rename table

ðŸ’¡ Use this repo to learn + practice + reference quickly.
